WEBVTT

01:33.052 --> 01:36.222
PA!
I FINISHED MY CHORES.
CAN I GO INTO TOWN?

01:36.389 --> 01:37.515
WHAT, ARE YOU
DONE ALREADY?

01:37.682 --> 01:39.017
YOU'RE A REAL WHIRLWIND
THIS MORNING.

01:39.184 --> 01:40.226
MUST BE
SOMETHING IMPORTANT.

01:40.393 --> 01:41.394
IT IS.

01:41.561 --> 01:42.520
ALL RIGHT. GO ON.
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

01:42.687 --> 01:43.480
THANKS, PA.

01:43.646 --> 01:44.689
Caroline: LAURA?

01:44.856 --> 01:45.899
YES, MA?

01:46.065 --> 01:47.776
HAVEN'T YOU NOTICED
THE WAY JACK'S BEEN

01:47.942 --> 01:49.319
SCRATCHING AND
FUSSING AT HIS EARS?

01:49.486 --> 01:50.653
NO, MA.

01:50.820 --> 01:52.071
WELL, HE HAS.

01:52.238 --> 01:53.865
IT LOOKS LIKE
HE'S BEEN RUNNING
IN THE TALL GRASS.

01:54.032 --> 01:56.242
MAYBE
HE'S GOT ANOTHER
FOXTAIL IN HIS EAR.

01:56.409 --> 01:58.661
WELL, COULDN'T CARRIE
PULL THEM OUT?

01:58.828 --> 02:01.414
CARRIE'S HELPING ME
BAKE A CAKE.

02:02.582 --> 02:05.043
LAURA,
JACK IS <i>YOUR</i> DOG.

02:05.210 --> 02:07.045
YOU'VE BEEN
NEGLECTING HIM LATELY.

02:07.212 --> 02:08.880
YOU CAN'T
JUST CAST HIM ASIDE

02:09.047 --> 02:11.257
LIKE A STITCH OF OLD
CLOTHES YOU'RE TIRED OF
AND FORGET HIM.

02:11.424 --> 02:14.928
MA, I PROMISE TO DO IT
WHEN I GET HOME,

02:15.094 --> 02:18.181
BUT I'VE GOT SOMETHING
REAL IMPORTANT TO TEND TO.

02:18.348 --> 02:20.600
LAURA, RIGHT NOW
YOU'LL TEND TO JACK.

02:20.767 --> 02:22.310
YES, MA'AM.

02:22.477 --> 02:23.978
[JACK BARKS]

02:40.453 --> 02:43.623
OH, SUCH A LOVELY DAY.

02:44.874 --> 02:47.627
A LOVELY DAY.

02:58.137 --> 03:00.723
MORNING!

03:02.016 --> 03:02.809
MORNING.

03:02.976 --> 03:05.311
BEAUTIFUL DAY, AIN'T IT?

03:05.478 --> 03:07.272
YES, IT IS.

03:07.438 --> 03:08.648
AS THE MAN SAID,

03:08.815 --> 03:09.858
CLEANLINESS IS

03:10.024 --> 03:11.317
NEXT TO GODLINESS.

03:11.484 --> 03:14.070
Crow: AMEN.

03:25.665 --> 03:29.252
AND I THOUGHT PERHAPS
IF WE INVITED HER TO THE
SUNDAY SERVICES TOMORROW,

03:29.419 --> 03:30.587
WE COULD ALL
GET TO KNOW HER BETTER.

03:30.753 --> 03:33.464
REVEREND ALDEN,
IN ALL DUE RESPECT,

03:33.631 --> 03:36.175
IF WE INVITE HER
INTO OUR CHURCH,

03:36.342 --> 03:38.511
WE WILL JUST BE
ENCOURAGING HER TO STAY.

03:38.678 --> 03:40.513
AND WE DON'T
WANT HER TO STAY.

03:40.680 --> 03:44.642
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
SHE'S ABOUT AS WELCOME
AS A PLAGUE OF LOCUSTS.

03:44.809 --> 03:46.811
IS IT SOMETHING SHE'S DONE?

03:46.978 --> 03:51.482
REVEREND ALDEN, PEOPLE
JUST DON'T LIVE IN A
HOUSE THAT ISN'T THERE.

03:51.649 --> 03:53.359
NOW, IF YOU ASK ME,

03:53.526 --> 03:55.778
SHE'S MORE THAN A LITTLE
BIT OFF HER ROCKER.

03:55.945 --> 03:58.406
YOU KNOW, I AGREE
WITH MRS. OLESON.

03:58.573 --> 03:59.866
AND THAT ANIMAL
OF HERS, CLYDE,

04:00.033 --> 04:01.367
IS AS CRAZY AS SHE IS.

04:01.534 --> 04:02.869
HE'S THE ONLY HORSE
I'VE EVER KNOWN

04:03.036 --> 04:04.829
THAT WOULD RATHER EAT
BEEF JERKY AND HARD CANDY

04:04.996 --> 04:07.206
THAN MY QUALITY OATS
AND HAY.

04:07.373 --> 04:09.709
REVEREND,
MY ONLY CONCERN IS
WITH THE CHILDREN.

04:09.876 --> 04:12.045
NOW, I THINK SHE SEEMS
HARMLESS ENOUGH.

04:12.211 --> 04:14.380
BUT, MISS BEADLE,

04:14.547 --> 04:15.715
LOOKS CAN
BE DECEIVING.

04:15.882 --> 04:17.717
NOW I HAVE TOLD MY
NELLIE AND MY WILLIE

04:17.884 --> 04:19.385
TO JUST KEEP AWAY
FROM HER,

04:19.552 --> 04:21.554
AND I CAN ONLY HOPE
AND PRAY

04:21.721 --> 04:23.389
THAT ALL OF
THE OTHER PARENTS
HAVE SENSE ENOUGH

04:23.556 --> 04:24.891
TO DO
THE SAME THING.

04:25.058 --> 04:28.061
MRS. OLESON,
IT SEEMS TO ME

04:28.227 --> 04:30.813
THAT THE CHRISTIAN THING TO DO
UNDER CIRCUMSTANCES--

04:30.980 --> 04:32.065
REVERED ALDEN,

04:32.231 --> 04:33.733
YOU STAY IN WALNUT GROVE

04:33.900 --> 04:35.151
ONLY TWO DAYS
OUT OF THE MONTH

04:35.318 --> 04:38.237
WHILE WE HAVE TO LIVE
WITH THAT--THAT CREATURE

04:38.404 --> 04:39.822
EVERY DAY.

04:39.989 --> 04:42.742
WELL, SHE SEEMS INTENT
ON STAYING.

04:42.909 --> 04:46.412
AND SINCE THE PROPERTY
WAS ABANDONED,

04:46.579 --> 04:49.874
LEGALLY SHE HAS EVERY RIGHT
TO STAY THERE.

04:50.041 --> 04:54.629
WELL, THEN, WE'LL JUST HAVE
TO LET NATURE RUN ITS COURSE.

04:54.796 --> 04:57.715
SHE COULDN'T POSSIBLY
SURVIVE THE COLD
OF THE WINTER

04:57.882 --> 05:00.927
IN THE CONFINES
OF THAT ROOT CELLAR.

05:01.094 --> 05:06.057
JACK, HOLD STILL!
JACK, YOU'RE BEING
STUBBORN AS A GOAT.

05:06.224 --> 05:09.477
NOW, WOULD YOU LET ME GET
THE FOXTAILS OUT OF YOUR EAR?

05:09.644 --> 05:11.729
JACK, STOP IT!

05:11.896 --> 05:13.356
[GROWLING BARK]

05:13.523 --> 05:15.942
JACK, COME BACK HERE!

05:16.109 --> 05:17.860
GET BACK HERE!

05:21.531 --> 05:23.825
I'M LOSING MY PATIENCE
WITH YOU.

05:23.992 --> 05:25.910
GET BACK HERE NOW!

05:26.077 --> 05:27.203
[RUFF]

05:27.370 --> 05:30.415
PUT THAT TOY DOWN.
I DON'T WANT TO PLAY.

05:30.581 --> 05:31.749
[RUFF]

05:31.916 --> 05:33.751
ALL RIGHT. GO AROUND
WITH FOXTAILS IN YOUR EARS.

05:33.918 --> 05:35.628
SEE IF I CARE.

05:41.884 --> 05:44.012
[JACK BARKING]

05:45.930 --> 05:47.932
[WHIMPERING]

05:59.819 --> 06:01.320
SORRY I'M LATE.

06:01.487 --> 06:03.489
I HAD TO STAY HOME
AND PICK FOXTAILS
OUT OF JACK'S EARS.

06:03.656 --> 06:05.616
ARE YOU SURE IT WASN'T
FLOWERS YOU WERE PICKING?

06:05.783 --> 06:07.368
I TOLD YOU
WHY I WAS LATE.

06:07.535 --> 06:09.579
JUST THOUGHT
IT'D BE NICE IF WE
BROUGHT HER SOMETHING.

06:09.746 --> 06:11.164
WILLIE THINKS
SHE'S A WITCH.

06:11.330 --> 06:12.999
YOU SHOULD HAVE
BROUGHT HER A DEAD RAT.

06:13.166 --> 06:16.252
STOP TALKING LIKE THAT,
AND LET'S GO.

06:16.419 --> 06:17.837
IT'S GOING TO GET DARK.

06:18.004 --> 06:19.589
IT'S STILL MORNING,
SILLY.

06:19.756 --> 06:21.591
COME ON.

06:36.647 --> 06:38.357
[CAW CAW]

06:38.524 --> 06:40.068
[CROW CAWING]

06:44.697 --> 06:46.157
[CAW CAW]

06:56.834 --> 06:57.710
SHE SAW US.

06:57.877 --> 06:59.003
SHH!

07:00.546 --> 07:02.006
Mary: COME ON.

07:07.929 --> 07:09.222
AHEM.

07:11.641 --> 07:14.227
UH, HI.

07:14.393 --> 07:16.729
WE CAME TO WELCOME YOU
TO WALNUT GROVE.

07:16.896 --> 07:18.189
MAY WE COME IN?

07:18.356 --> 07:23.778
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS KNOCK,
AND THE DOOR WILL BE OPENED.

07:24.946 --> 07:26.656
COME ON.

07:34.622 --> 07:35.832
KNOCK KNOCK.

07:35.998 --> 07:38.251
IS ANYBODY HOME?

07:39.669 --> 07:41.129
[CAW]

07:47.593 --> 07:50.388
MY! MY!

07:50.555 --> 07:52.598
WHAT HAVE WE HERE?

07:52.765 --> 07:54.684
WE'RE THE WELCOMING
COMMITTEE.

07:54.851 --> 07:56.686
OH.

07:56.853 --> 08:00.398
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE,
CHILDREN.

08:00.565 --> 08:04.277
YOU'RE TOO KIND.

08:04.443 --> 08:07.113
PLEASE, WON'T YOU
COME INTO MY HOUSE?

08:23.462 --> 08:28.384
I'M KEZIA HORN, AND
THIS IS PARROT POLLY.

08:28.551 --> 08:31.554
THAT'S NOT A PARROT.
IT'S A CROW.

08:31.721 --> 08:32.805
OH. SHH.

08:32.972 --> 08:34.807
HE THINKS
HE'S A PARROT.

08:34.974 --> 08:37.476
I WOULDN'T WANT
TO DISAPPOINT HIM.

08:37.643 --> 08:39.478
Crow: WANT A
PIECE OF CANDY.

08:39.645 --> 08:42.523
OH. I DON'T
HAVE NO MORE.

08:42.690 --> 08:43.774
LAND SAKES, POLLY.

08:43.941 --> 08:47.486
YOU AND CLYDE HAVE
GOT A SWEET TOOTH LATELY.

08:47.653 --> 08:49.197
HA HA HA!

08:49.363 --> 08:54.785
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO HAVE TEA AND ORANGES
WHEN YOU CAME A-KNOCKING.

08:54.952 --> 08:57.371
WOULD YOU
LIKE TO JOIN ME?

08:57.538 --> 09:00.374
CAN I HAVE COFFEE
LIKE MY PA DRINKS?

09:00.541 --> 09:02.501
OH, I THINK
I CAN FIX THAT.

09:02.668 --> 09:03.753
YES.

09:14.847 --> 09:20.144
YES, WE'LL BE WANTING...
7 CUPS AND SAUCERS.

09:22.480 --> 09:28.486
IT WAS WHISKEY JAKE CURRY
WHAT GIVE ME THESE CUPS.

09:28.653 --> 09:33.241
HE KNEW I HAD AN EYE
FOR PRETTY THINGS.

09:36.077 --> 09:37.912
BEAUTIFUL, AREN'T THEY?

09:38.079 --> 09:40.039
YEAH,
THEY SURE ARE.

09:40.206 --> 09:43.584
BEAUTIFUL. YEAH.
HA HA.

09:43.751 --> 09:45.836
[BLOWS]

09:46.003 --> 09:48.089
[WHISTLING LIKE A TEA KETTLE]

09:50.549 --> 09:53.427
WATER'S BOILING.

09:56.639 --> 09:58.557
[CAW CAW]

09:58.724 --> 10:00.559
NICE AND WARM.

10:00.726 --> 10:01.811
YEAH.

10:01.978 --> 10:03.688
HERE'S YOUR COFFEE,

10:03.854 --> 10:06.065
ALL NICE AND HOT
LIKE YOU ASKED FOR.

10:06.232 --> 10:07.358
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

10:07.525 --> 10:09.193
I DON'T SEE
ANY COFFEE.

10:09.360 --> 10:10.569
NELLIE!

10:10.736 --> 10:12.571
WELL, THIS IS DUMB.
I DON'T SEE ANY COFFEE.

10:12.738 --> 10:14.657
THEN YOU'LL
HAVE TO LEAVE.

10:14.824 --> 10:16.242
WHAT?

10:16.409 --> 10:19.245
YOU CAN'T STAY
IF YOU CAN'T SEE IT.

10:19.412 --> 10:21.205
YOU MIGHT ACCIDENTALLY
BURN YOURSELF.

10:21.372 --> 10:24.750
THEY CAN'T SEE IT.
THEY HAVE TO GO, TOO.

10:24.917 --> 10:26.377
I CAN SEE IT.

10:26.544 --> 10:27.503
ME, TOO.

10:27.670 --> 10:28.963
WILLIE?

10:29.130 --> 10:32.925
NICE AND STRONG,
JUST LIKE PA DRINKS IT.

10:36.595 --> 10:38.556
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

10:46.063 --> 10:50.818
SOME PEOPLE NEVER REMEMBER
TO CLOSE THE DOOR.

10:50.985 --> 10:52.945
HA HA!

10:57.783 --> 10:59.493
CARRIE, ON THE CAKE.

10:59.660 --> 11:01.787
YES, MA.

11:01.954 --> 11:03.664
MOM, WE MET
KEZIA HORN TODAY!

11:03.831 --> 11:05.708
AND SHE
READ OUR FORTUNES
FROM OUR TEA LEAVES.

11:05.875 --> 11:07.001
THAT'S NICE,
GIRLS.

11:07.168 --> 11:08.461
I'M GOING TO RAISE
A BIG FAMILY SOMEDAY--

11:08.627 --> 11:09.712
BIGGER THAN OURS, MA.

11:09.879 --> 11:12.465
AND I'M GOING
TO TRAVEL FAR AND WIDE.

11:12.631 --> 11:14.300
BEFORE YOU
TRAVEL ANYWHERE,
YOUNG LADY,

11:14.467 --> 11:16.135
I WANT YOU TO TAKE
A SHORT TRIP
OUT TO THE YARD

11:16.302 --> 11:18.804
AND FINISH TAKING
THE FOXTAILS OUT
OF JACK'S EARS.

11:18.971 --> 11:21.307
I TRIED TO, MA,
BUT JACK WOULDN'T LET ME.

11:21.474 --> 11:22.850
WELL, TRY HARDER.

11:23.017 --> 11:24.977
AND THE NEXT TIME I TELL
YOU TO DO SOMETHING,
YOUNG LADY,

11:25.144 --> 11:26.437
I WANT YOU TO DO IT.

11:26.604 --> 11:28.731
YES, MA'AM.

11:32.693 --> 11:36.989
JACK! JACK!

11:37.156 --> 11:38.657
PA, HAVE YOU SEEN JACK?

11:38.824 --> 11:40.493
I CAN'T FIND HIM
ANYWHERE!

11:40.659 --> 11:41.994
LAST TIME I SAW HIM,
HONEY,

11:42.161 --> 11:43.287
HE WAS ASLEEP
IN THE BARN.

11:43.454 --> 11:45.164
THANKS!

11:48.667 --> 11:51.379
JACK, ARE YOU IN HERE?

11:53.214 --> 11:55.049
GOOD-FOR-NOTHING DOG.

11:55.216 --> 11:57.343
ARE YOU SLEEPING BACK HERE?

11:57.510 --> 12:00.721
BOY, ARE YOU GOING TO GET IT
WHEN I FIND YOU.

12:00.888 --> 12:04.475
JACK, WHY DIDN'T YOU COME
WHEN I CALLED YOU?

12:04.642 --> 12:07.311
GET UP, YOU LAZY DOG.

12:07.478 --> 12:09.730
I SAID GET UP!

12:13.651 --> 12:14.860
JACK?

12:19.115 --> 12:20.449
JACK?

12:20.616 --> 12:22.201
[HAMMERING OUTSIDE]

12:23.619 --> 12:25.204
PA, COME QUICK!

12:29.375 --> 12:31.293
HALF-PINT!

12:31.460 --> 12:34.213
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
WHAT ARE YOU YELLING ABOUT?

13:09.039 --> 13:11.250
HE'S DEAD,
ISN'T HE, PA?

13:33.939 --> 13:39.445
JACK TRAVELED
A LOT OF MILES WITH US
ACROSS A LOT OF RIVERS.

13:39.612 --> 13:42.531
HE WAS
KIND OF OLD AND TIRED.

13:42.698 --> 13:44.825
HIS TIME HAD COME.

13:47.077 --> 13:48.954
JUST WANTED
TO GO TO SLEEP QUIET

13:49.121 --> 13:50.915
SO HE WOULDN'T
MAKE A FUSS.

13:55.002 --> 14:00.466
WHEN HE
NEEDED ME THE MOST,
I WASN'T THERE.

14:00.633 --> 14:05.095
HEY, WE ALWAYS FEEL THAT WHEN
WE LOSE SOMEBODY CLOSE TO US.

14:06.138 --> 14:08.474
WISHING
WE COULD BE WITH THEM,

14:08.641 --> 14:10.851
TELL THEM HOW MUCH
WE LOVE THEM.

14:11.018 --> 14:13.938
LIFE DOESN'T
ALWAYS WORK OUT THAT WAY.

14:16.023 --> 14:17.816
TELL YOU,
YOU AND THAT OLD DOG
HAD SOMETHING SPECIAL.

14:17.983 --> 14:21.320
HAD SOMETHING A LOT OF PEOPLE
DON'T HAVE IN A WHOLE LIFETIME.

14:28.244 --> 14:30.496
PA...

14:30.663 --> 14:34.583
CAN WE BURY HIM
ON THE LOW HILL
OVER THE MEADOW

14:34.750 --> 14:36.210
WHERE HE LOVED
TO PLAY?

14:36.377 --> 14:39.713
YOU BET. I THINK THAT
WOULD BE A FINE PLACE.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.882
LOVE THAT PLACE.

14:44.677 --> 14:46.095
WHY DON'T YOU
GO ON IN THE HOUSE,

14:46.262 --> 14:48.180
AND I'LL...
I'LL BUNDLE HIM UP.

14:48.347 --> 14:49.890
I'LL DO IT, PA.

15:31.807 --> 15:34.476
HALF-PINT, SUN'LL
BE GOING DOWN SOON.

15:36.353 --> 15:39.940
CAN I BE ALONE
WITH JACK A MOMENT, PA?

15:43.485 --> 15:45.112
YEAH.

15:51.577 --> 15:54.872
I DIDN'T MEAN THE THINGS
I SAID TO YOU, JACK.

15:56.999 --> 16:00.419
YOU'RE THE BEST DOG
IN THE WHOLE WORLD,

16:00.586 --> 16:03.797
THE BEST DOG
A GIRL COULD EVER HAVE.

16:05.883 --> 16:10.346
AND I'M GOING TO SAY A PRAYER
FOR YOU EVERY NIGHT

16:10.512 --> 16:16.185
SO--SO THAT GOD KEEP YOU SAFE
AND WARM IN YOUR NEW BED.

16:22.733 --> 16:24.193
JACK.

16:56.642 --> 16:59.978
THERE'S KEZIA. HI!
HI!

17:02.815 --> 17:05.567
I WONDER WHY KEZIA
ISN'T COMING TO CHURCH.

17:05.734 --> 17:07.653
BECAUSE, CHILD,
SHE'S A HEATHEN.

17:07.820 --> 17:11.115
WELL, MAYBE SHE WORSHIPS
AT HOME LIKE WE DO
SOMETIMES.

17:18.956 --> 17:19.873
Caroline:
MORNING, REVEREND.

17:20.040 --> 17:20.833
CAROLINE.

17:20.999 --> 17:22.501
REVEREND.

17:22.668 --> 17:23.836
CHARLES.

17:38.058 --> 17:39.685
Reverend: SHALL WE PRAY?

17:39.852 --> 17:45.357
All:
OUR FATHER WHO ART IN HEAVEN,
HALLOWED BE THY NAME.

17:45.524 --> 17:51.613
THY KINGDOM COME,
THY WILL BE DONE ON EARTH
AS IT IS IN HEAVEN.

17:51.780 --> 17:55.033
GIVE US THIS DAY
OUR DAILY BREAD...

18:23.896 --> 18:26.440
HEY, YOU MUTT! GIT!

18:28.233 --> 18:32.029
DAGGONE DOG
KEEPS COMING AROUND.

18:37.159 --> 18:40.704
THAT NO-ACCOUNT CUR
WAS TRYING TO STEAL
YOUR BACON.

18:40.871 --> 18:42.706
WELL, NO CRIME
BEING HUNGRY.

18:42.873 --> 18:44.124
SOONER THAT BACON
DISAPPEARS,

18:44.291 --> 18:46.126
THE SOONER
I'LL BE RID OF HIM.

19:29.711 --> 19:32.089
HA HA HA!
HEY, YOU LITTLE BANDIT.

19:32.256 --> 19:33.799
HOW'D YOU GET
ON THE WAGON, HUH?

19:33.966 --> 19:37.803
ALL RIGHT. SIT AND
RELAX. ENJOY THE RIDE.

19:59.908 --> 20:02.160
GOT TO FESS UP, DOC.

20:02.327 --> 20:05.247
I TRIED LAYING
ON THEM BOARDS
LIKE YOU SAID.

20:05.414 --> 20:08.083
IT GOT A MITE
DISAGREEABLE
AFTER A WHILE.

20:08.250 --> 20:10.919
NOW, JONATHAN, IF YOU
WANT THAT BACK OF YOURS
TO LOOSEN UP,

20:11.086 --> 20:13.714
YOU GOTTA STAY OFF YOUR FEET
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.

20:13.881 --> 20:15.299
I CAN'T DO THAT,
DOC.

20:15.465 --> 20:17.009
I GOT ME A FIELD
NEEDS PLOWING.

20:17.175 --> 20:18.719
THAT'S WHAT I FIGURED.

20:18.886 --> 20:22.055
NOW HERE. GET YOURSELF
SOME SOAP LINIMENT,
CAMPHOR, AND WINTERGREEN,

20:22.222 --> 20:24.266
AND HAVE ALICE RUB IT IN
REAL GOOD AT NIGHT.

20:24.433 --> 20:26.518
MUCH OBLIGED, DOC.

20:26.685 --> 20:28.353
DON'T EXPECT
ANY MIRACLES.

20:28.520 --> 20:30.314
WHAT YOU NEED
IS SOME REST.

20:30.480 --> 20:32.274
YEAH.

20:34.234 --> 20:36.904
STUBBORN.
MULE-HEADED.

20:45.996 --> 20:48.498
HEY, WE'RE HOME.

20:53.587 --> 20:56.840
CHARLES!
WHERE DID YOU FIND HIM?

20:57.007 --> 20:59.843
I DIDN'T EXACTLY FIND HIM.

21:00.010 --> 21:01.553
IT'S MORE LIKE HE FOUND ME.

21:01.720 --> 21:03.138
IS HE REALLY OURS
TO KEEP?

21:03.305 --> 21:05.265
I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.
WHERE'S HALF-PINT?

21:05.432 --> 21:06.850
IN THE BARN.

21:07.017 --> 21:09.311
WE'LL SEE IF
THIS LITTLE FELLOW
CAN CHEER HER UP.

21:09.478 --> 21:11.980
COME ON!
COME ON, BOY!

21:12.147 --> 21:14.691
[BARKING]

21:24.076 --> 21:26.036
HEY, HALF-PINT.
I GOT A LITTLE
SURPRISE FOR YOU.

21:26.203 --> 21:28.246
HEY. WELL,
COME ON, BOY.

21:28.413 --> 21:31.083
LOOK WHAT JUMPED ON
MY WAGON ON THE WAY
OUT OF MANKATO.

21:31.249 --> 21:33.168
HE'S JUST A STRAY,
BUT HE'S A DARNED
GOOD DOG.

21:33.335 --> 21:34.294
HE'S SMART.

21:34.461 --> 21:37.756
HA HA! OH,
HE REALLY LIKES YOU.

21:37.923 --> 21:40.717
HE CAN BE YOURS
IF YOU WANT HIM.

21:42.344 --> 21:43.345
DON'T WANT HIM!

21:43.512 --> 21:45.222
DON'T WANT ANY DOG.

21:45.389 --> 21:46.807
AW, COME ON.

21:46.974 --> 21:49.309
HE'S JUST TRYING TO GIVE
YOU A LITTLE LOVING,
THAT'S ALL.

21:50.310 --> 21:52.896
I DON'T WANT HIM!

22:03.615 --> 22:05.200
AH, WE TRIED.

22:05.367 --> 22:06.868
COME ON, BOY.

22:08.578 --> 22:10.497
[WHIMPERING]

22:20.298 --> 22:22.009
MA, CAN'T WE
LET HIM IN?

22:22.175 --> 22:24.803
NOT WHILE WE'RE EATING.
HE'LL PICK UP BAD HABITS.

22:24.970 --> 22:26.388
HE'S HUNGRY.

22:26.555 --> 22:30.475
Caroline:
WELL, YOU CAN GIVE HIM
SOME SCRAPS AFTER DINNER.

22:30.642 --> 22:33.437
WELL, BEING IN
A STRANGE PLACE AND ALL,

22:33.603 --> 22:35.647
HE'S PROBABLY FRIGHTENED
TO DEATH OUT THERE ALONE.

22:35.814 --> 22:37.065
[DOG WHIMPERING]

22:39.234 --> 22:42.738
ALL RIGHT. YOU CAN LET HIM IN,
BUT JUST FOR TONIGHT.

22:42.904 --> 22:44.531
I'LL DO IT.

22:55.083 --> 22:56.334
WE HAVE TO NAME HIM.

22:56.501 --> 22:58.628
HEY, YOU'RE RIGHT.
I FORGOT ALL ABOUT THAT.

22:58.795 --> 23:00.005
ANYBODY GOT ANY IDEAS?

23:00.172 --> 23:01.965
WE COULD CALL HIM TOM.

23:02.132 --> 23:04.926
SALLY NORTH
HAS A DOG NAMED TOM.

23:05.093 --> 23:08.346
SALLY NORTH
HAS A CAT.

23:08.513 --> 23:10.348
OH, YEAH.

23:10.515 --> 23:12.059
HE DOES LOOK LIKE
HE'S WEARING A MASK,

23:12.225 --> 23:13.685
AND I DID CATCH HIM STEALING
WHEN I FIRST SAW HIM.

23:13.852 --> 23:14.936
WHY DON'T WE
CALL HIM BANDIT?

23:15.103 --> 23:17.147
OH, THAT NAME
REALLY SUITS HIM.

23:17.314 --> 23:18.398
YEAH.

23:18.565 --> 23:20.901
Caroline:
WHAT DO YOU THINK, LAURA?

23:21.068 --> 23:23.153
I DON'T CARE
WHAT YOU NAME HIM.

23:23.320 --> 23:24.654
MAY I
PLEASE BE EXCUSED?

23:24.821 --> 23:26.573
Caroline: YOU'VE HARDLY
TOUCHED YOUR SUPPER.

23:26.740 --> 23:28.658
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

23:29.743 --> 23:31.578
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

23:43.381 --> 23:44.883
[WHIMPERING]

24:00.774 --> 24:02.484
[SAW BUZZING]

24:08.240 --> 24:09.074
OH!

24:09.241 --> 24:10.784
LORD ALMIGHTY!

24:10.951 --> 24:12.536
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU
QUIT TRYING TO WORK

24:12.702 --> 24:14.121
UNTIL THAT BACK
OF YOURS HEALS UP?

24:14.287 --> 24:15.997
NAW. IT'S GOING
TO BE ALL RIGHT.

24:16.164 --> 24:17.916
SURE YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

24:18.083 --> 24:19.334
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE MOANING
AND GROANING ALL THE TIME.

24:19.501 --> 24:22.420
AH, IT'S--I GOTTA
TAKE MY MEDICINE NOW.

24:22.587 --> 24:23.797
I'LL BE LIKE A NEW MAN.

24:23.964 --> 24:25.841
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

24:26.007 --> 24:27.676
SUIT YOURSELF.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.110
GOOD MORNING, MR. GARVEY.

24:45.277 --> 24:46.444
JUMPING JEHOSHAPHAT,
CHILD.

24:46.611 --> 24:47.946
YOU SHOULDN'T SNEAK UP
ON A MAN LIKE THAT.

24:48.113 --> 24:51.408
OH, I WASN'T SNEAKING.
I WAS JUST GOING TO SCHOOL.

24:51.575 --> 24:53.326
OH, YEAH. WELL...

24:53.493 --> 24:55.245
WHAT'S IN THE BOTTLE?

24:55.412 --> 24:57.205
UH, THAT'S, UH...

24:57.372 --> 24:59.291
OH, THAT'S JUST
THE MEDICINE THAT
DOC BAKER GOT FOR ME.

24:59.457 --> 25:02.669
IT'S THE BIGGEST BOTTLE
OF MEDICINE I EVER SAW.

25:02.836 --> 25:05.380
YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,
AS BIG AS I AM,

25:05.547 --> 25:07.007
WHY, I GOTTA HAVE A LOT.

25:07.174 --> 25:08.550
DON'T LIKE THE STUFF.

25:08.717 --> 25:10.886
I'LL BET KEZIA'D
HAVE A BETTER CURE.

25:11.052 --> 25:12.179
THAT OLD MAGPIE?

25:12.345 --> 25:13.847
SHE'S CRAZIER
THAN A LOON.

25:14.014 --> 25:16.558
BUT SHE KNOWS EVERYTHING
THERE IS TO KNOW
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

25:16.725 --> 25:18.310
YEAH, WELL, I--

25:18.476 --> 25:20.187
MAYBE I'LL GO ON
AND SEE HER, HUH?

25:20.353 --> 25:21.438
SEE YA.

25:21.605 --> 25:22.731
SEE YA.

25:26.067 --> 25:29.279
OH, DADBURN IT.

25:36.077 --> 25:37.662
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
KEZIA?

25:37.829 --> 25:40.248
HUH?

25:40.415 --> 25:44.002
IT'S A PERFECT DAY
FOR HANGING OUT
THE WASH.

25:44.169 --> 25:46.213
HA HA HA!
GOOD IDEA.

25:49.132 --> 25:51.885
Laura: GET AWAY!
I SAID, GET AWAY!

25:52.052 --> 25:53.386
I DON'T WANT YOU
FOLLOWING ME.

25:53.553 --> 25:55.889
♪ LAURA'S DOG
IS UGLY AS A HOG ♪

25:56.056 --> 25:57.224
♪ LAURA'S DOG ♪
GET AWAY,
I SAID!

25:57.390 --> 25:58.767
♪ IS UGLY AS A HOG ♪

25:58.934 --> 26:00.227
♪ LAURA'S DOG ♪
HE'S NOT
MY DOG!

26:00.393 --> 26:01.770
♪ IS UGLY AS A HOG ♪

26:01.937 --> 26:03.563
Nellie: THEN
WHOSE IS HE?
Laura:
HE'S A STRAY!

26:03.730 --> 26:05.690
♪ LAURA'S DOG
IS UGLY AS A HOG ♪

26:05.857 --> 26:07.525
HE'S NOT MY DOG!

26:07.692 --> 26:10.320
♪ LAURA'S DOG IS UGLY
AS A HOG ♪
HE'S NOT MINE!

26:12.113 --> 26:14.115
GO AWAY!

26:35.845 --> 26:36.680
[CROW CAWS]

26:36.846 --> 26:38.223
UH, MORNING.

26:38.390 --> 26:40.767
HOW DO.

26:40.934 --> 26:42.227
I WAS, UH...

26:42.394 --> 26:44.896
I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD HAVE A FEW...

26:45.063 --> 26:46.231
HAVE A FEW WORDS
WITH YOU.

26:46.398 --> 26:49.651
OH, ALWAYS A-HANKERING
AFTER GOOD CONVERSATION.

26:49.818 --> 26:53.488
HEY! POLLY,
GET OFF THE MAN'S HEAD.

26:53.655 --> 26:55.573
[CAW CAW]

26:55.740 --> 26:57.033
COME ON IN.

26:57.200 --> 27:00.453
MIND YOU,
USE THE DOOR.

27:05.875 --> 27:08.795
UH, NAME'S GARVEY,
MA'AM.

27:08.962 --> 27:10.755
MY NAME'S KEZIA.

27:10.922 --> 27:12.716
SOME PEOPLE
CALL ME KIZZY.

27:12.882 --> 27:14.718
SOME PEOPLE
CALL ME CRAZY.

27:14.884 --> 27:17.846
SOME PEOPLE DON'T
CALL ME AT ALL.

27:18.013 --> 27:19.597
HEH HEH HEH.

27:20.849 --> 27:24.019
UH, ME AND MARY
WAS JUST KIND OF JAWING,

27:24.185 --> 27:25.979
AND, UH, SHE SAID--

27:26.146 --> 27:30.775
WELL--WELL, DOC BAKER'S
GIVEN ME A WHOLE PASSELFUL
OF REMEDIES FOR MY CRICK.

27:30.942 --> 27:32.319
AIN'T NONE
OF THEM WORKING,

27:32.485 --> 27:33.987
AND I WAS JUST
KIND OF WONDERING--

27:34.154 --> 27:37.407
ACTUALLY
KIND OF HOPING IF MAYBE
YOU'D BE HAVING A CURE.

27:37.574 --> 27:39.784
A PAIN? DULL OR SHARP?

27:39.951 --> 27:42.287
WELL, KIND OF--
KIND OF NAGGING.

27:42.454 --> 27:46.166
YOU KNOW, LIKE A ROPE
PULLING DOWN LOW ON MY BACK.

27:46.333 --> 27:49.627
YOU GOT A TOUCH OF
THE "TIZ"--RHEUMATISM.

27:49.794 --> 27:53.298
I'VE HAD IT MYSELF
NOW AND THEN.

27:53.465 --> 27:54.632
YOU GOT A CURE?

27:54.799 --> 27:57.552
I GOT THE VERY THING
FOR IT.

27:57.719 --> 28:01.181
YOU WANT SOME PARAFFIN,
SOME MINERAL OIL,

28:01.348 --> 28:03.058
AND A GOOD STIFF BRUSH

28:03.224 --> 28:05.769
AND A TUB OF HOT WATER.

28:05.935 --> 28:10.565
WHAT KIND OF SKIVVIES
DO YOU BED IN?

28:12.025 --> 28:12.901
WELL, UH...

28:13.068 --> 28:14.152
AHEM.

28:14.319 --> 28:16.821
I'LL, UH...I'LL BE
IN MY RED FLANNELS.

28:16.988 --> 28:21.785
THEM'S JUST THE THING
FOR KEEPING THE HEAT IN.

28:21.951 --> 28:25.830
YEAH. OH,
WITH THE PAIN THAT LOW,

28:25.997 --> 28:28.249
BE SURE
TO KEEP YOUR FLAP SHUT.

28:28.416 --> 28:30.752
YES'M.

28:32.670 --> 28:34.005
HERE YOU GO.

28:34.172 --> 28:36.466
THIS IS WHAT
WE'RE GONNA DO.

28:49.354 --> 28:51.481
MR. HANSON?

28:51.648 --> 28:53.983
Man:
HE WENT HOME SICK.

28:56.986 --> 28:59.572
NELS. DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE YOUR VOICE.

28:59.739 --> 29:01.074
WELL, HANSON
FEELING POORLY, IS HE?

29:01.241 --> 29:03.159
OH, YEAH, YEAH.

29:03.326 --> 29:05.203
HE WAS--HE WAS DIZZY.

29:05.370 --> 29:06.830
HE WAS VERY DIZZY.

29:06.996 --> 29:08.873
HA HA HA!

29:09.040 --> 29:11.334
WHAT'S--
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

29:11.501 --> 29:14.129
I DON'T KNOW.
HA HA HA!

29:14.295 --> 29:15.922
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

29:16.089 --> 29:18.216
OH, COULDN'T BE BETTER.

29:18.383 --> 29:20.844
THE TROUBLE IS
I'M VERY THIRSTY.

29:21.010 --> 29:23.596
I JUST CAN'T GET ENOUGH
OF THIS WATER.

29:25.140 --> 29:26.975
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU
AT THE MEETING TONIGHT.

29:27.142 --> 29:28.893
WHAT MEETING?

29:29.060 --> 29:31.229
WELL, THE MEETING
AT THE CHURCH.

29:31.396 --> 29:32.772
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO DECIDE

29:32.939 --> 29:34.399
WHETHER WE'RE
GOING TO LET KEZIA
IN THE CONGREGATION.

29:34.566 --> 29:36.443
OH. THAT MEETING.

29:36.609 --> 29:39.112
I'LL BE THERE.

29:40.530 --> 29:42.157
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

29:42.323 --> 29:44.909
FINE AND DANDY.

29:46.161 --> 29:47.078
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

29:47.245 --> 29:49.664
YOU BETCHA, CHARLES!

30:00.675 --> 30:02.302
OH.

30:24.240 --> 30:25.033
[RUFF]

30:25.200 --> 30:27.535
BE QUIET.
GO ON. GET AWAY.

30:27.702 --> 30:29.370
[BARKING]

30:36.794 --> 30:39.631
THAT'S JACK'S TOY.
GET AWAY.

30:39.797 --> 30:41.925
[RUFF RUFF RUFF]

30:42.091 --> 30:43.343
I SAID GET AWAY!

30:43.510 --> 30:45.970
GO ON. GET AWAY.

30:49.641 --> 30:51.684
[BARKING]

31:07.283 --> 31:08.535
GET AWAY.

31:08.701 --> 31:10.078
GO AWAY.

31:10.245 --> 31:12.080
SHOO!

31:12.247 --> 31:13.706
GO AWAY.

31:25.802 --> 31:27.095
I WANT TO THANK YOU,
CHARLES,

31:27.262 --> 31:29.931
FOR HELPING ME TRY
TO PREVAIL UPON THEM
TO RECONSIDER,

31:30.098 --> 31:31.808
EVEN IF OUR PLEAS
DID FALL ON DEAF EARS.

31:31.975 --> 31:34.894
THE WAY THEY CARRIED ON,
YOU'D THINK SHE BROUGHT
THE PLAGUE TO TOWN.

31:35.061 --> 31:37.021
WELL, I FIND MYSELF
CAUGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF THIS.

31:37.188 --> 31:38.356
MINISTER OF
THE CONGREGATION,

31:38.523 --> 31:41.276
I'M THE SHEPHERD
OF THE FLOCK, BUT...

31:41.442 --> 31:45.238
IF THE FLOCK
WON'T TAKE IN ONE
OF ITS LOST SHEEP,

31:45.405 --> 31:49.867
WHY, I MUST ABIDE BY
THEIR WISHES OR RISK
LOSING THEM ALL.

31:50.034 --> 31:52.787
YOU KNOW, I WOULDN'T
HAVE SAID THAT WHEN
I WAS A YOUNGER MAN.

31:52.954 --> 31:54.497
WELL, I'LL
TELL HER TOMORROW.

31:54.664 --> 31:57.000
I'D RATHER IT BE ME
THAN TO HAVE THEM
CAST HER OUT

31:57.166 --> 32:00.044
WITHOUT A KIND WORD
OR A BLESSING.

32:00.211 --> 32:02.088
I DON'T ENVY YOU,
REVEREND.

32:02.255 --> 32:03.047
GOOD NIGHT.

32:03.214 --> 32:04.966
GOOD NIGHT, CHARLES.

32:11.306 --> 32:15.310
[FAINT SNORING]

32:23.818 --> 32:26.904
[SNORING]

32:32.577 --> 32:35.330
NELS.
HUH? WHAT?

32:41.586 --> 32:43.212
NELS?
[LIGHT SLAP]

32:43.379 --> 32:45.256
I VOTE NAY.

32:45.423 --> 32:47.508
NELS, THE MEETING'S OVER.
YOUR WIFE'S GONE HOME.

32:47.675 --> 32:51.888
OH, THAT EXPLAINS WHY
IT'S SO QUIET IN HERE.

32:52.055 --> 32:53.514
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

32:53.681 --> 32:56.601
SURE. I'M JUST THIRSTY,
THAT'S ALL.

32:56.768 --> 32:58.853
I NEED A DRINK OF WATER.

33:13.284 --> 33:15.703
[DOOR OPENS, THUDDING]

33:22.502 --> 33:25.213
THEY'RE CONCERNED
ABOUT YOUR WELFARE.

33:25.380 --> 33:26.631
YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY PROTECTION

33:26.798 --> 33:28.174
AGAINST THE COLD
WINTER MONTHS AHEAD.

33:28.341 --> 33:31.678
THE COLD YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT, REVEREND,

33:31.844 --> 33:34.472
HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH WINTER.

33:34.639 --> 33:40.603
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT'S
DOING THE PROTECTING.

33:42.438 --> 33:44.315
OH, DON'T GET ME WRONG.

33:44.482 --> 33:46.150
I APPRECIATE YOUR CALLING,

33:46.317 --> 33:52.657
BUT YOU SEE,
THIS ISN'T THE FIRST TIME
I'VE BEEN ASKED TO MOVE ON,

33:52.824 --> 33:55.702
AND I RECKON
IT WON'T BE THE LAST.

33:55.868 --> 33:58.788
YOU SEE,
I'M 80 YEARS OLD.

33:58.955 --> 34:00.248
OUTLIVED TWO HUSBANDS,

34:00.415 --> 34:02.667
BEEN EVERYWHERE
THERE IS TO BE,

34:02.834 --> 34:05.336
SEEN EVERYTHING
THERE IS TO SEE,

34:05.503 --> 34:12.301
AND THE ONE THING
I'VE FOUND IS THE PEOPLE
ARE THE SAME EVERYWHERE--

34:12.468 --> 34:16.222
KIND OF SET
IN THEIR WAYS,

34:16.389 --> 34:20.935
AFRAID OF ANYONE
WHO'S DIFFERENT TO THEM.

34:21.102 --> 34:24.981
IT'S GOT NOTHING TO DO
WITH BEING GOOD OR BAD

34:25.148 --> 34:29.026
OR GENEROUS OR STINGY.

34:29.193 --> 34:32.029
IT'S HUMAN NATURE.

34:33.656 --> 34:36.325
DON'T EVER CHANGE,
KEZIA.

34:36.492 --> 34:39.704
IT'S THE PEOPLE
WHO ARE DIFFERENT
WHO MOVE THE MOUNTAINS.

34:39.871 --> 34:42.248
HAVING LIVED
AS LONG AS I HAVE,

34:42.415 --> 34:44.876
I'M NOT ABOUT TO,

34:45.042 --> 34:49.839
BUT I KNOW
WHEN I DON'T BELONG.

34:50.006 --> 34:55.553
ONLY REASON
I STAYED THIS LONG
WAS THE CHILDREN.

34:55.720 --> 35:01.058
THEY REACHED OUT AND
MADE IT ALL WORTHWHILE.

35:02.351 --> 35:03.728
WHERE WILL YOU GO?

35:03.895 --> 35:10.860
UH...WELL, I DON'T
RIGHT KNOW AT THE MOMENT,

35:11.027 --> 35:14.071
BUT DON'T YOU GO
WORRYING NONE, REVEREND.

35:14.238 --> 35:17.241
I'LL GET BY.

35:18.409 --> 35:20.912
I'M SURE YOU WILL,
KEZIA.

35:22.413 --> 35:24.999
I'M SURE YOU WILL.

35:26.918 --> 35:29.962
WELL,
I'D BEST BE GOING.

35:31.339 --> 35:35.593
MIND YOU, DON'T FORGET
TO CLOSE THE DOOR.

36:08.626 --> 36:14.173
PA! MA SAID I COULD GO
INTO TOWN A LITTLE BIT EARLY
AND VISIT WITH KEZIA.

36:14.340 --> 36:16.008
ALL RIGHT, DARLIN'.
WE'LL SEE YOU IN CHURCH.

36:16.175 --> 36:18.636
THANKS, PA.

36:24.684 --> 36:27.436
[RUFF RUFF]

36:35.152 --> 36:37.446
[CAW]

36:37.613 --> 36:41.450
Laura: DON'T FOLLOW ME!
I DON'T WANT YOU! GO AWAY!

36:41.617 --> 36:42.785
GO AWAY!

36:42.952 --> 36:44.537
GO ON! GET AWAY!

36:44.704 --> 36:46.247
[BANDIT BARKING]

36:46.414 --> 36:48.457
GO HOME!

36:48.624 --> 36:53.504
I DON'T WANT YOU FOLLOWING ME.
NOW GO HOME!

36:53.671 --> 36:57.592
GO HOME.

36:57.758 --> 36:59.343
[BANDIT YELPS]

37:07.393 --> 37:08.519
KNOCK KNOCK.

37:08.686 --> 37:11.439
DOOR'S OPEN.
COME ON IN.

37:14.108 --> 37:19.113
SEEMS YOU WERE
A MITE CROSS WITH
THAT THERE DOG OF YOURS.

37:19.280 --> 37:22.241
HE'S NOT MY DOG.
HE'S A STRAY.

37:22.408 --> 37:23.826
JACK WAS MY DOG.

37:23.993 --> 37:28.289
HE WAS THE BEST DOG
IN THE WHOLE WORLD
AND SMART, TOO.

37:28.456 --> 37:29.916
BUT HE DIED.

37:31.375 --> 37:33.502
I KNOW
HOW YOU'RE FEELING.

37:33.669 --> 37:39.091
LOST MY FIRST MAN
WHISKEY JAKE
OUT AT SEA.

37:39.258 --> 37:45.181
I SAYS, "KEZIA,
THERE AIN'T NO MAN
ON THIS EARTH

37:45.348 --> 37:49.518
THAT WILL EVER FILL
HIS SHOES."

37:49.685 --> 37:56.567
THAT WAS
BEFORE I MET
SMILIN' WILLIE HORN.

37:56.734 --> 38:02.573
YOU KNOW, A PERSON
GETS TO BE LONELY.

38:02.740 --> 38:07.828
GETS HANKERING
AFTER BEING NEEDED.

38:07.995 --> 38:10.373
BUT JACK AND I
HAD SOMETHING SPECIAL.

38:10.539 --> 38:11.999
NO DOG WILL
EVER TAKE HIS PLACE.

38:12.166 --> 38:16.295
THAT THERE HEART
OF YOURS WILL ALWAYS
HAVE A PLACE FOR JACK.

38:16.462 --> 38:21.759
BUT I BET IT'S GOT
A LOT MORE ROOM IN IT
FOR LOVING.

38:21.926 --> 38:23.427
BUT I CAN'T LOVE
SOME DUMB OLD DOG

38:23.594 --> 38:25.554
WHO GOES AROUND CHASING
HIS TAIL ALL THE TIME.

38:25.721 --> 38:28.599
PRETTY CLEVER CRITTER
IF YOU ASK ME.

38:28.766 --> 38:30.601
YOU WOULDN'T PLAY
WITH HIM,

38:30.768 --> 38:33.145
SO HE MADE DO WITH
WHAT HE HAD.

38:34.855 --> 38:37.733
KIND OF LIKE YOU PRETENDING
YOU HAVE A REAL HOUSE

38:37.900 --> 38:40.277
WHEN YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY WALLS OR A ROOF.

38:40.444 --> 38:45.157
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO HAVE WALLS AND A ROOF
TO HAVE HOSPITALITY.

38:48.577 --> 38:50.371
I WISH YOU WEREN'T
GOING, KEZIA.

38:50.538 --> 38:54.333
WELL, FOLKS HAVEN'T
TAKEN TOO KINDLY TO ME.

38:54.500 --> 38:58.921
I CAN'T STAY IF I
HAVEN'T GOT A HOME HERE.

38:59.088 --> 39:02.466
IF YOU HAVE A HOME,
WOULD YOU STAY?

39:02.633 --> 39:04.760
OH, THERE'S A FEELING--

39:04.927 --> 39:08.389
A FEELING OF BELONGING,
OF BEING NEEDED.

39:08.556 --> 39:11.642
YOU'RE A LUCKY GIRL.
YOU'VE GOT BOTH.

39:11.809 --> 39:16.981
ME, WELL, UH,
I'M KIND OF LIKE
THAT LITTLE MUTT.

39:17.148 --> 39:19.817
I GOT A LOT
OF LOVING TO GIVE,

39:19.984 --> 39:27.491
BUT I DON'T SEEM TO
KIND OF FIND PEOPLE
WHO WILL TAKE IT.

39:27.658 --> 39:33.372
I RECKON BANDIT AND ME
IS DIFFERENT FROM MOST.

39:33.539 --> 39:37.835
WELL, IT AIN'T CHRISTIAN
FOR FOLKS NOT TO INVITE
YOU INTO CHURCH.

39:38.002 --> 39:42.548
OH, MAYBE. BUT IT'S NO
WORSE THAN DRIVING OFF
A LITTLE DOG

39:42.715 --> 39:45.342
WHO JUST WANTS
TO LOVE YOU, IS IT?

39:47.261 --> 39:49.638
NO.

39:49.805 --> 39:52.600
IT'S JUST THAT...

39:52.767 --> 39:55.352
OH, COME ON.
OUT WITH IT.

39:56.812 --> 39:59.690
WELL, I LOVED JACK SO.

39:59.857 --> 40:02.359
WHEN HE DIED...

40:03.861 --> 40:09.742
YES, AND YOU'RE
AFRAID TO LOVE BANDIT
BECAUSE HE MIGHT DIE,

40:09.909 --> 40:13.621
AND YOU'D HURT
ALL OVER AGAIN.

40:13.788 --> 40:14.997
YES'M.

40:15.164 --> 40:18.084
WELL, LET ME TELL
YOU THIS, CHILD.

40:18.250 --> 40:20.711
HURTING GOES AWAY.

40:20.878 --> 40:23.380
LOVE, NEVER.

40:23.547 --> 40:28.677
LOVING IS THE
GREATEST GIFT THE
GOOD LORD GAVE US.

40:28.844 --> 40:31.097
DON'T WASTE IT.

40:31.263 --> 40:35.267
NOT FOR A MOMENT.

40:37.228 --> 40:38.687
I GOTTA GO FIND BANDIT.

40:38.854 --> 40:40.397
I'LL BE BACK.

40:42.900 --> 40:44.068
I LOVE YOU.

40:44.235 --> 40:47.154
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
CHILD.

40:47.321 --> 40:48.739
NOW GIT.

40:48.906 --> 40:50.407
OK.

41:07.216 --> 41:08.968
BANDIT!

41:20.354 --> 41:22.231
BANDIT!

41:25.359 --> 41:27.611
[COUGHING AND GASPING]

41:27.778 --> 41:30.406
BANDIT!

41:30.573 --> 41:32.032
COME ON, BANDIT!

41:32.199 --> 41:33.367
COME ON!

41:33.534 --> 41:35.286
COME ON, BANDIT!

41:38.038 --> 41:40.291
BANDIT!

41:55.764 --> 41:57.224
BANDIT.

41:59.101 --> 42:01.562
BANDIT! COME BACK!

42:01.729 --> 42:03.564
I DIDN'T MEAN IT!

42:03.731 --> 42:06.400
PLEASE COME BACK!

42:06.567 --> 42:09.570
BANDIT...

42:09.737 --> 42:11.947
I DO LOVE YOU.

42:12.114 --> 42:13.908
I LOVE YOU, BANDIT.

42:14.074 --> 42:16.660
PLEASE DON'T BE AFRAID.

42:16.827 --> 42:19.872
I LOVE YOU.

43:13.300 --> 43:15.135
BANDIT.

43:15.302 --> 43:16.929
MY BANDIT.

43:19.181 --> 43:20.641
MY BANDIT.

43:31.151 --> 43:32.695
HEY, UH, MISS KEZIA?

44:15.279 --> 44:18.115
COME ON, POLLY. WE'RE OFF.

44:20.909 --> 44:22.119
[CAW CAW]

44:22.286 --> 44:25.247
COME ON, CLYDE.
WHENEVER YOU'VE A MIND TO.

44:25.414 --> 44:27.249
COME ON. THERE.

44:46.477 --> 44:50.939
♪ ONWARD CHRISTIAN SOLDIERS ♪

44:51.106 --> 44:54.610
♪ MARCHING AS TO WAR ♪

44:54.777 --> 44:58.906
♪ WITH THE CROSS OF JESUS ♪

44:59.073 --> 45:03.535
♪ GOING ON BEFORE ♪

45:05.829 --> 45:07.539
Laura: REVEREND ALDEN?

45:07.706 --> 45:11.168
REVEREND ALDEN,
MISS KEZIA'S GONE.

45:11.335 --> 45:14.004
WE CAN'T LET HER GO.

45:14.171 --> 45:17.674
SHE LEFT BECAUSE SHE THOUGHT
SHE DIDN'T BELONG HERE.

45:17.841 --> 45:19.760
BUT SHE WAS WRONG.

45:19.927 --> 45:23.138
WE NEED HER HERE.

45:23.305 --> 45:25.557
SHE'S GOT SO MUCH LOVE
TO GIVE.

45:27.184 --> 45:30.562
SHE MADE ME SEE I NEEDED BANDIT
AS MUCH AS HE NEEDED ME.

45:32.731 --> 45:36.693
SHE WAS GOOD AND KIND
TO EVERYONE WHO GAVE HER
HALF A CHANCE.

45:37.778 --> 45:40.614
SO WHAT
IF SHE WAS DIFFERENT?

45:40.781 --> 45:42.199
WE'RE ALL DIFFERENT.

45:42.366 --> 45:47.037
IF WE KNOCKED ON
HER MAKE-BELIEVE DOOR,
SHE LET US IN.

45:47.204 --> 45:49.998
BUT WHEN SHE KNOCKED,
NOBODY HEARD HER.

45:51.875 --> 45:55.629
SEEK AND
YE SHALL FIND.

45:55.796 --> 46:00.509
KNOCK AND IT SHALL
BE OPENED TO YOU.

46:00.676 --> 46:05.681
HE PREACHED HIS GOSPEL
AS HE WALKED BY
THE SEA OF GALILEE,

46:05.848 --> 46:08.016
TALKING OF LOVE
AND KINDNESS.

46:09.435 --> 46:11.228
HEALING THE SICK.

46:12.354 --> 46:15.524
GIVING HOPE TO
THE POOR IN SPIRIT.

46:15.691 --> 46:21.572
AS I STAND BEFORE YOU,
I ASK YOU...

46:24.408 --> 46:27.744
IF THIS GENTLE STRANGER...

46:27.911 --> 46:31.790
WHO MADE THE BLIND
TO SEE...

46:31.957 --> 46:34.126
AND THE LAME TO WALK...

46:36.837 --> 46:41.049
IF HE WERE TO COME TODAY
TO OUR TOWN OF WALNUT GROVE...

46:44.761 --> 46:48.098
WOULD YOU CAST HIM OUT
JUST BECAUSE HE WAS DIFFERENT?

46:51.143 --> 46:54.438
Mrs. Oleson:
WHAT WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
HAS ALREADY BEEN VOTED ON.

46:54.605 --> 46:57.191
NOW, I FOR ONE AM NOT
ABOUT TO CHANGE MY VOTE.

46:57.357 --> 46:59.943
ALL IN AGREEMENT,
PLEASE RAISE YOUR HANDS.

47:08.410 --> 47:11.997
YAHOO! COME ON!
LET'S GO GET HER!

47:46.823 --> 47:49.660
Laura: KEZIA DIDN'T
LEAVE WALNUT GROVE THAT DAY.

47:49.826 --> 47:52.162
SHE STAYED WITH US
FOR THE REST OF HER YEARS...

47:53.497 --> 47:54.873
AND SO DID MY DOG...

47:55.040 --> 47:56.708
BANDIT.
